

	 
       A difficult goodbye  Im watching a show on our television set But nothing anymore, seems the same There is an emptiness, where you once were And I wonder who is to blame  But now whenever I go in your room It is you, that I dont see Im supposed to visit you later today But I am not yet filled with glee  I should be excited, to see you again But inside, I am mostly scared You tought me many thing throughout my life But for this Dad, I am unprepared  I dont know how to say goodbye And its something I may never learn Some people seem to do it fine It may be a blessing that I must earn  But either way, you are not here And because of that, I am scared Not because you are not here But because Im so badly unprepared.
     
    
